@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}

@section Styles {
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/HomeStyle/HomeStyle.css">
}

<div class="container">
    <div class="banner">
        <div class="hero">
            <img src="../Images/Alangilan-background.jpg" alt="University Entrance" loading="lazy">
            <div class="odd-shape">
                <h1>Build Skills With Online Courses</h1>
                <p>
                    At BatStateU, we are committed to render extension service to depressed and underserved
                    communities,
                    as well as to share our expertise in science, technology, education, management, and research
                    with
                    public and private agencies/organizations that need our services.
                </p>
                <a href="@Url.Action("ProgramCatalog", "Home")" class="cta-button">Explore Courses</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trainings">
        <div class="center-text">
            <h1 class="agenda-title">12 Agendas</h1>
            <p class="agenda-description">Explore the 12 agendas that drive innovation and growth at BatStateU.</p>
        </div>
        <section class="layout">
            <section class="content">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/BISIG.jpg" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">BatStateU Inclusive Social Innovation for Regional Growth (BISIG)</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">The BatStateU Inclusive Social Innovation for Regional Growth (BISIG) is a program designed to develop innovative solutions—such as new concepts, processes, products, or organizational changes—that enhance the well-being of families and communities. It focuses on addressing socio-economic and environmental challenges by fostering a collaborative policy framework. BISIG brings together public, non-profit, and private sectors to create a strong alliance for inclusive social innovation and drive regional growth.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/LEAF.jpg" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Livelihood and Other Entrepreneurship related on Agri-Fisheries (LEAF)</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">The Livelihood and Entrepreneurship related to Agri-Fisheries (LEAF) program aims to identify and develop potential extension programs that provide livelihood and entrepreneurship opportunities in the agri-fisheries sector. Its goal is to reduce poverty and inequality by creating jobs, generating income, and moving vulnerable households toward sustainable livelihoods and economic stability. The program supports the goals of zero poverty and decent work, aligning with the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) of 2030.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/ENRCPR.jpg" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Environment and Natural Resources Conservation, Protection and Rehabilitation</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">The program focuses on preserving biodiversity and enhancing the productive capacity of watershed rainforests to support sustainable, resource-based watershed communities. It achieves this through research-driven extension programs, projects, and activities aimed at environmental conservation and sustainable development.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/SAEI.png" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Smart Analytics for Engineering Innovation</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">The program aims to promote research-based extension to help various data users, including small to medium enterprises, industries, local governments, policymakers, educators, students, and other stakeholders, effectively utilize data for informed decision-making. It focuses on leveraging innovations like smart predictive informatics tools to interpret complex data, improving daily productivity while supporting broader goals of economic competitiveness.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/BIDANI.png" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Adopt-A-Municipality / Social Development Through BINADI Implementation</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">This program is designed to create, implement, and assess high-impact, research-based community development projects. It uses an approach that promotes social development in adopted communities or schools, focusing on sustainable nutrition through a locally driven and integrated management system. The goal is to foster long-term community well-being and development.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/CO.jpg" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Community Outreach</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">The agenda seeks to involve University stakeholders—students, parents, teachers, staff, personnel, and alumni—in humanitarian activities and public service. It emphasizes collaboration with community-based organizations and institutions to promote a just, loving, equitable, and humane society, while enhancing the quality of life at the grassroots level.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/TVET.jpg" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Technical-Vocational Education And Training (TVET)</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">The TVET Program aims to equip the economy with skilled and capable workers. It trains citizens to contribute to growth and poverty reduction by offering training opportunities to all social groups, ensuring equal access without discrimination.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/TTAU.jpg" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Technology Transfer, And Adoption / Utilization</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">This agenda focuses on supporting faculty and students in developing pathways for research-based technology transfer, enhancing faculty technological capabilities for more effective extension services. It aims to facilitate technology assessment, transfer, adoption, and utilization of research outputs. Additionally, it seeks to assist community and industry sectors through technological advancement and innovation, promoting the transfer of high-impact research outputs for their utilization, while ensuring the quality of research-based technologies through ongoing assessment and monitoring.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/TAAS.jpg" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Technical Assistance And Advisory Services</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">This initiative aims to identify strategies to enhance the productivity of local government units, small and medium enterprises, government and non-government agencies, and educational institutions through technical support and capacity building, including stakeholder consultations. Expected outputs include support for policy reforms and capacity building in business regulation, access to finance, and public-private partnerships (PPP).</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/PESODEV.jpg" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Parents' Empowerment Thru Social Development (PESODEV)</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">PESODEV aims to offer livelihood, gender and development, responsible parenting, and socio-cultural training and activities for parents. The goal is to empower them to become active participants in their communities, including within the University system.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/GED.png" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title"> Gender And Development</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">The program aims to integrate a gender perspective into the curriculum, research, and operations of the University. It seeks to institutionalize gender-responsive mechanisms, develop gender-aware members of the academic community, and establish partnerships with stakeholders and experts. Additionally, it focuses on collaboration in the planning, implementation, and evaluation of Gender and Development (GAD) programs and projects, and on upgrading facilities to address stakeholders' gender concerns.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                            <div class="course-cards">
                                <div class="course-card">
                                    <img src="../Images/DRRMDPR.jpg" alt="Beginner">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">Disaster Risk Reduction And Management And Disaster Preparedness And Response / Climate Change Adoption (DRRM and DPR / CCA)</h5>
                                    <div class="card-description">The program aims to foster a safe and secure environment for individuals and communities. Specifically, it seeks to raise awareness of Disaster Risk Reduction Management (DRRM) and Disaster Preparedness/Climate Change Adaptation (DPR/CCA), enhance community members' safety and preparedness, and educate them on proper emergency response and evacuation procedures. Additionally, the program focuses on ensuring the health and safety of people during calamities and disasters and training volunteers to address the needs of communities in such situations.</div>
                                </div>
                                <!-- Add more course cards as needed -->
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>